  "title": "Data Engineer – MLOps & AI Platforms",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a <strong>Senior Data Engineer with MLOps experience</strong> to build and operate scalable data platforms that support machine learning, AI, and LLM use cases. This role focuses on enabling end-to-end ML pipelines, from data ingestion and feature engineering to model deployment and monitoring.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Design and optimize large-scale data pipelines using <strong>Hadoop, Spark, and PySpark</strong></p></li><li><p>Build batch and real-time data processing workflows for AI/ML workloads</p></li><li><p>Implement <strong>MLOps pipelines</strong> for model training, deployment, and monitoring</p></li><li><p>Develop scalable feature engineering pipelines using <strong>Python</strong></p></li><li><p>Collaborate with ML engineers and data scientists to productionize AI/ML and LLM solutions</p></li><li><p>Support cloud-based AI platforms on <strong>AWS / Azure / GCP</strong></p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Strong experience in <strong>Hadoop, Apache Spark / PySpark</strong></p></li><li><p>Proficiency in <strong>Python</strong>; <strong>Scala</strong> is an advantage</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience with <strong>MLOps tools</strong> (Airflow, MLflow, Kubeflow, SageMaker, Azure ML)</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of <strong>machine learning workflows</strong> and AI systems</p></li><li><p>Experience with <strong>Docker, Kubernetes</strong>, and cloud platforms</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Nice to Have</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Exposure to <strong>LLMs, NLP, or advanced AI use cases</strong></p></li><li><p>Experience with streaming tools (Kafka, NiFi)</p></li><li><p>Consulting or enterprise project experience</p></li></ul>",
